The '''Medal "In Commemoration of the 1000th Anniversary of Kazan"''' ({{lang-ru|<U+041C><U+0435><U+0434><U+0430><U+043B><U+044C> <U+00AB><U+0412> <U+043F><U+0430><U+043C><U+044F><U+0442><U+044C> 1000-<U+043B><U+0435><U+0442><U+0438><U+044F> <U+041A><U+0430><U+0437><U+0430><U+043D><U+0438><U+00BB>}} is a state commemorative medal of the [[Russian Federation]].  It was issued to denote the 1000th anniversary of the foundation of [[Kazan]], the [[capital city]] of [[Tatarstan]].

== Medal History ==
The Medal "In Commemoration of the 1000th Anniversary of Kazan" was established on June 30, 2005 by Presidential Decree <U+2116> 762<ref name="decree762">{{cite web | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of June 30, 2005 | publisher = ZAKONY of Russia, Legal texts on line | date = 1992-07-02 | url = http://lawrussia.ru/texts/legal_339/doc339a375x124.htm | format = HTML | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-02-17}}</ref>.    

== Medal Statute ==
The Medal "In Commemoration of the 1000th Anniversary of Kazan" was awarded to Kazan residents who fought in the Great Patriotic War of 1941-1945, wartime workers who worked during the Great Patriotic War of 1941-1945 in the city of Kazan for at least six months or that were awarded orders and medals of the Soviet Union for their dedicated work in the Great Patriotic War of 1941 - 1945, veterans of labour; and to other citizens who have made a significant contribution to the development of the city of Kazan<ref name=" decree762"/>.

Presidential Decree 1099 of September 7, 2010<ref name="decree1099">{{cite web  | authorlink = Russian Government | title = Decree of the President of the Russian Federation of September 7, 2010 No 1099 | publisher = Russian Gazette | date = 2010-09-07 | url = http://www.rg.ru/2010/09/15/nagrady-dok.html | format = HTML | language = Russian | accessdate =2012-02-15}}</ref> dictated that although still bestowed by the state, that commemorative medals were no longer to be considered "awards" in the distinction/reward sense of the word, but were solely for the purpose of denoting a special event or date.

== Medal Description ==
The Medal "In Commemoration of the 1000th Anniversary of Kazan" is a circular 32mm in diameter brass medal with raised rims on both sides.  On its [[obverse]], in relief, the image of the Kazan Kremlin surrounded by the inscription "In Commemoration of the 1000th Anniversary of Kazan" ({{lang-ru|"<U+0412> <U+043F><U+0430><U+043C><U+044F><U+0442><U+044C> 1000-<U+043B><U+0435><U+0442><U+0438><U+044F>}}) <U+041A><U+0430><U+0437><U+0430><U+043D><U+0438>".  On its reverse, the emblem of the city of Kazan between branches of oak at right and laurel at left.  At the bottom, the relief inscription "1005 - 2005"<ref name=" decree762"/>. 

The medal is suspended by a ring through the award's suspension loop to a standard Russian pentagonal mount covered with a 24mm wide overlapping tricolour silk [[moir<U+00E9>]] ribbon with a 10mm wide green stripe on the left, a 4mm wide white stripe in the center and a 10mm wide red stripe on the right<ref name=" decree762"/>.

